Pages = {71-83},
Month = {JUN},
Abstract = {A fuzzified neural network copes with fuzzy signals and/or weights so
   that the information about the uncertainty of input and output can be
   served in the training process. Since learning process is the main
   function of fuzzy neural networks, in this study, we focus on review and
   comparison of the existing learning algorithms, so that the theoretical
   achievement and the application agenda of each considered algorithm can
   be clarified from the aspects of computation complexity and accuracy.
   Two numerical examples of nonlinear mapping of fuzzy numbers and
   realization of fuzzy IF-THEN rules are used for illustration and
