Month = {FEB 28},
Abstract = {In this study, a novel selective \& nonlinear neural network ensemble
   model, i.e. NSNNEIPCABag, is proposed for economic forecasting. In this
   model, some different training subsets are first generated by bagging
   algorithm. Then the feature extraction technique, improved principal
   component analysis (IPCA), and then the IPCA approach is also used to
   extract their data features to train individual networks, and to select
   the appropriate number of ensemble members from the available networks.
   Finally, the selected members are aggregated into a nonlinear ensemble
   model with support vector regression (SVR). For illustration and testing
   purposes, the proposed ensemble model is applied for economic
   forecasting.},
